{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778227499,"nonce":"qgYbg1G6Lth4rYTvddzCAeX9fvc=","message":"**Integrating note: flavor-B follow-ups settled (both negative at canonical operating point).**\n\nTwo pending follow-ups (`74bfd86` induced-gain analyser on flavor-B trained models; `97c227a` Riccati flavor-(b) extension) now resolved; bundling here as cross-cutting because the *joint* result is bigger than either taken alone.\n\n**Headline.** Both pre-registered hypotheses for the simple (a) ⊊ (b) thesis are **not supported** at the canonical operating point.\n\n**Subagent C — induced gain on flavor-B trained models.** 45 replicates (3 η_max × 3 seeds × 5 reps); γ_sd flavor-B median **154.78** vs flavor-A baseline **163.39** (excluding `mult_single` rep_0 known-degenerate); ratio **0.947** — a ~5% reduction, within methodological noise. γ_sd is **flat in η_max** (152.5 / 156.2 / 154.8); the U-shape in training ctrl_loss (§6.4 of synthesis doc) does not appear in γ_sd, suggesting it is a saddle-dynamics / fused-loss reporting artifact. Surprise positive on γ_sp (sensory channel): flavor-B is comparable to flavor-A minimax despite never training against that channel. Cross-ref `74bfd86` comment `7344b34`; cross-method comparison at `results/part2_5/induced_gain_flavor_b/cross_method_comparison.md`.\n\n**Subagent D — flavor-(b) Riccati synthesis (S-procedure quadratic-stability lift).** New `solve_hinf_riccati_modelclass` API; flavor-(a) interface untouched. γ*^(b) on rlrmp ($k=10$) at η=0.1 is +2.0% vs γ*^(a) (0.009618 vs 0.009427); on the C\u0026S regime (faithful Eq. 15 Q,R) γ*^(b) is essentially flat for η ≤ 1 because C\u0026S Q dominates the augmentation. **The xfailed `test_cs_faithful_qr_velocity_inflation` does NOT pass under flavor-(b)**: Δv at 1.5γ*^(b) stays ≤ 0 and goes more negative as η increases (η=10 gives Δv=−4.11%; η=100 gives −52.93%). Mechanism: Q-augmentation damps the controller, lowering forward velocity — opposite of the C\u0026S signature. The conservative quadratic-stability lift is *insufficient* to recover the C\u0026S \"robust = faster reach\" effect. Cross-refs `97c227a` and `c99ad9d`.\n\n**Tier-shift implications: none.** The (a) ⊊ (b) thesis is *constrained* but not refuted — both probes are conservative (single-canonical-reach worst-case operator norm; quadratic-stability bound), and the gap may be finer than either captures. No analyses tier rerank is warranted from this evidence.\n\n**Natural next analyses (not filed as placeholder issues):** direction-projected induced gain (project onto trained-against ΔA directions instead of worst-case); μ-synthesis or trajectory-coupled time-varying B_w(x_t) for tighter analytical bounds; operating-point sensitivity (reach geometry / SISU level / horizon sweep). Will file when actually planned.\n\nCanonical write-up for external review: `results/flavor_a_vs_b/synthesis.md` (§7.1, §7.2, §8.0 carry the joint-result discussion).","files":null}]}